items.synopsis: Australia bring India's first innings to a close after lunch on day three of the ICC World Test Championship Final at The Oval, taking with them a handy lead. Follow all the action in our live blog.

title.children: Australia claim handy first-innings lead over India on day three of WTC final

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: So a very healthy lead indeed for Australia, but it could have been much worse for India if not for the work of Ajinkya Rahane and Shardul Thakur today. That partnership has given India life, and should something remarkable happen in this game they will look back at that stand as a turning point. The highlight of the day though was Cam Green's catch to remove Rahane, a moment of brilliance to punctuate a sloppy day in the field for the Aussies. It came at a critical time, and signalled the beginning of the end for India. So now the Aussie top order will return to the crease looking to take the game away from India. They could happily bat for a day or more now to make it a sure thing, but on a tricky pitch that is no foregone conclusion. Big hour coming up before tea.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: India all out 296, trailing by 173 runs

children.content: So a very healthy lead indeed for Australia, but it could have been much worse for India if not for the work of Ajinkya Rahane and Shardul Thakur today. That partnership has given India life, and should something remarkable happen in this game they will look back at that stand as a turning point.

The highlight of the day though was Cam Green's catch to remove Rahane, a moment of brilliance to punctuate a sloppy day in the field for the Aussies. It came at a critical time, and signalled the beginning of the end for India.

So now the Aussie top order will return to the crease looking to take the game away from India. They could happily bat for a day or more now to make it a sure thing, but on a tricky pitch that is no foregone conclusion. Big hour coming up before tea.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Scott Boland has done it again! KS Bharat took guard, a deep breath and prepared for his first ball of the day. Turns out that's the extent of his involvement. It was another Boland beauty, nibbling at the right hander from a perfect length. It found the gap between bat and pad and shattered middle and off. It's trademark Boland, and it's a big early breakthrough for Australia. India on the ropes already.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: BOWLED HIM! Boland strikes second ball of the day!

It was another Boland beauty, nibbling at the right hander from a perfect length. It found the gap between bat and pad and shattered middle and off. It's trademark Boland, and it's a big early breakthrough for Australia.
